OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Henry Leach
OL,5,F"When we were in there the Germans had
OL,6,Fa machine gun. The platoon was
OL,7,Ftrapped. I got fed up with that and
OL,8,Fwent up round onto the other side and
OL,9,Ftook a few shots of them over the
OL,10,Fvalley and of course the machine post
OL,11,Fwe couldn't see.
OL,13,F"I covered the withdrawal of the rest
OL,14,Fof the platoon out of the valley and
OL,15,Fjoined them on the other side of the
OL,16,Fvillage.''
OL,18,F"There was tension of course. When we
OL,19,Fstopped we dug trenches big enough for
OL,20,Fone or two.
